input_str: I hate doing dishes. No matter what, I always end up with more dish water on myself than in the sink. It’s like a child using their face to eat chocolate cake but 100% less endearing. It’s mostly just damp. I think I just get overly enthusiastic with my dish washing movements, going for speed rather than quality of cleanliness.
